// H9a acceptance area (e) — subagent spawn + mid-stream cancellation.
// A `mode: subagent` loom whose one untyped query drives a real turn against a
// freshly spawned isolated `AgentSession`. The production subagent drive injects
// a bounded mid-stream cancel (through the injected Clock) so cancellation
// propagates into the in-flight turn and surfaces `Err(cancelled)` to loom code;
// the spawned session's committed turns are left unmutated (ERR-8), so no
// `loom/runtime/internal-error` is emitted. The observed cancellation is echoed
// on the user-visible channel so the black-box `pi -p` capture can score it.
@`Reply with a short one-line greeting.`
